<HEAD>About 30 People Massacred On Mindanao Island</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: To CORRECT to guerrillas, sted villagers, SUB 6th graf, `Villagers
exchanges ...' Picks up 7th, `Maralit ...'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Communist rebels raided a mountain village in a remote area of <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> island and massacred about 30 people as they worshipped in a <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> church, the military said Monday. The raiders beheaded three people, including a <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> minister, before fleeing, the report said. Lt. Col. <PERSON> Cresencio </PERSON> <PERSON> Maralit </PERSON>, spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Philippine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Constabulary </ORGANIZATION>, said the incident occurred early Sunday in the village of <LOCATION> Rano </LOCATION>, about 640 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Maralit </PERSON> said many of the villagers had joined an anti-Communist vigilante group and had refused to pay `` revolutionary taxes'' to the communist <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION>. According to <PERSON> Maralit </PERSON>, about 40 members of the <PERSON> Ubo </PERSON> and <PERSON> Bagobo </PERSON> tribes had gathered inside a <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christ </ORGANIZATION> chapel for morning worship when about 100 guerrillas arrived. Guerrillas exchanged gunfire for about 15 minutes with members of the congregation, who were armed, <PERSON> Maralit </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Maralit </PERSON> identified the dead pastor as <PERSON> Abadi </PERSON> <PERSON> Ayap </PERSON>. But a denomination official in <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> said records indicated no such pastor by that name. Bishop <PERSON> Erme </PERSON> <PERSON> Camba </PERSON>, secretary-general of the denomination, said the victim could have been a lay pastor. The bishop said he was still trying to verify the report. The <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christ </ORGANIZATION> has been widely criticized by the military for alleged links with <ORGANIZATION> Communist </ORGANIZATION> rebels because of the denomination's outspoken stand on human rights. In the past, most beheadings in <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> have been carried out by religious fanatics who are frequently used by the military to fight the Communists.
