<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Communist rebels attacked anti-Marxist villagers at a church in a remote village and killed at least 39 people, including women and children, officials said today. Two of the dead _ a <ORGANIZATION> Protestant </ORGANIZATION> lay leader and his brother _ were beheaded during the incident, which occurred Sunday at a <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Church </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Christ </ORGANIZATION> chapel in <LOCATION> Rano </LOCATION>, on <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> island about 640 miles southeast of <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION>. At least eight people were wounded, officials said. The military said the death toll could be higher because the rebels carted away their casualties. A survivor claimed two rebels were killed. A church official in <LOCATION> Manila </LOCATION> said the 39 confirmed dead were congregation members. Lt. Col. <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Maneja </PERSON>, deputy commander of <LOCATION> Davao </LOCATION> <LOCATION> del </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sur </LOCATION> province, said about 100 <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> guerrillas entered the village looking for the leader of a group of local anti-communist vigilantes. <PERSON> Maneja </PERSON> said details were unclear, but apparently someone indicated that vigilante leader <PERSON> Ruben </PERSON> <PERSON> Ayap </PERSON> was inside the church and shooting broke out. <PERSON> Ayap </PERSON> was killed along with his two brothers, <PERSON> Abadi </PERSON> and <PERSON> Clemente </PERSON>. <PERSON> Abadi </PERSON> <PERSON> Ayap </PERSON>, head of the laymen's group at the church, and his brother <PERSON> Clemente </PERSON> were beheaded, the military said. <PERSON> Regina </PERSON> <PERSON> Dominguez </PERSON>, 41, whose daughter was killed in the shooting, said the rebels were angry because villagers had formed an anti-co