riticized by the military for alleged links with communist rebels because of the denomination's outspoken stand on human rights. Sunday's incident occurred in an area of southeastern <LOCATION> Mindanao </LOCATION> where the military has organized armed anti-communist vigilante groups to counter rebels in remote areas. Various church organizations have accused the vigilantes of widespread human rights abuses. The <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> People </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> has been waging a 20-year insurgency to establish a communist state in the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>.
