<HEAD>Caped Crusader Drives Nation Batty, Propels All-Time Box Office Tallies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Moviegoers went batty over the Caped Crusader, with `` Batman'' taking in a record $ 43.6 million and giving <LOCATION> Hollywood </LOCATION> its biggest weekend ever. The film, starring <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Keaton </PERSON> as <PERSON> Batman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> Nicholson </PERSON> as the archvillian Joker, helped the nation's theaters over the weekend gross a record $ 95 million-plus overall. `` Batman's'' debut on 2,193 screens surpassed the three-day record $ 29.4 million set just a week earlier by `` Ghostbusters II,'' studio receipts showed today. `` This is tremendous. It is the biggest weekend ever in the history of the business,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Krier </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which tracks box-office performance. The previous overall box-office record for a three-day weekend was $ 92 million, said <PERSON> Krier </PERSON>. `` Batman'' also broke every daily record. It took in $ 15.6 million on Friday to beat the $ 10.2 million by `` Ghostbusters II'' a week earlier, $ 14.8 million on Saturday to top the record $ 11.2 million by `` Indiana <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> and the Last Crusade'' on May 27, and $ 13.2 million on Sunday to top the May 28 mark of $ 10.2 million by `` Last Crusade.'' In second place was <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Honey, I Shrunk the Kids,'' which grossed $ 14.2 million and broke all opening weekend box office tallies for that studio, said <PERSON> Krier </PERSON>. `` Three Men and a Baby'' was Disney's previous leader with $ 13.1 million over the 1987-88 New Year's weekend. `` Ghostbusters II'' was third with $ 14 million, `` Indiana <PERSON> Jones </PERSON> and the Last Crusade'' was fourth with $ 7.8 million and `` Dead Poets Society'' was fifth with $ 7.6 million.
