<HEAD>For Release Saturday, July 8</HEAD>
<HEAD>Today In History</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Today is Saturday, July 8, the 189th day of 1989. There are 176 days left in the year. Today's highlight in history: One hundred years ago, `` The Wall Street Journal'' was first published. On this date: In 1663, King Charles II of <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> granted a charter to <LOCATION> Rhode </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION>. In 1776, a Colonel <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Nixon </PERSON> gave the first public reading of the Declaration of Independence to a crowd gathered at Independence Square in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION>. In 1891, future president <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Harding </PERSON> married <PERSON> Florence </PERSON> <PERSON> K. </PERSON> <PERSON> DeWolfe </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Marion </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>. In 1896, <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Jennings </PERSON> <PERSON> Bryan </PERSON> captivated the Democratic national convention in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> with his `` cross of gold'' speech. In 1907, <PERSON> Florenz </PERSON> <PERSON> Ziegfeld </PERSON> staged his first `` Follies,'' on the roof of the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Theater. In 1919, President <PERSON> Woodrow </PERSON> <PERSON> Wilson </PERSON> received a tumultuous welcome in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> after his return from the <ORGANIZATION> Versailles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Conference </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>. In 1947, demolition work began in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> to make way for the new permanent headquarters of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>. In 1950, Gen. <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> <PERSON> MacArthur </PERSON> was named commander-in-chief of <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> forces in <LOCATION> Korea </LOCATION>. In 1959, Maj. <PERSON> Dale </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Buis </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Imperial </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, and Master Sgt. <PERSON> Chester </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ovnand </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Copperas </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Cove </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>, became the first American soldiers to be killed during the Vietnam War. In 1975, President <PERSON> Gerald </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Ford </PERSON> announced he would seek the Republican nomination for the presidency in 1976. Ten years ago: President <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Carter </PERSON> continued his summit on domestic issues at Camp David, <LOCATION> Md. </LOCATION>, consulting with a procession of state and national officials. Five years ago: <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> McEnroe </PERSON> defeated <PERSON> Jimmy </PERSON> <PERSON> Connors </PERSON> in straight sets, 6-1, 6-1, 6-2 to become the first <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> man in 46 years to capture back-to-back Wimbledon tennis titles. One year ago: <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s parliamentary speaker, <PERSON> Hashemi </PERSON> <PERSON> Rafsanjani </PERSON>, said his nation would not seek revenge against the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> for the shooting down of an Iranian jetliner over the <LOCATION> Persian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> that resulted in the deaths of all 290 people on board. Today's birthdays: Former <LOCATION> Michigan </LOCATION> Gov. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Romney </PERSON> is 82. Critic <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerr </PERSON> is 76. Singer <PERSON> Billy </PERSON> <PERSON> Eckstein </PERSON> is 75. ABC News President <PERSON> Roone </PERSON> <PERSON> Arledge </PERSON> is 58. Singer <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> is 54. Ballerina <PERSON> Cynthia </PERSON> <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> is 43. Actress <PERSON> Kim </PERSON> <PERSON> Darby </PERSON> is 41. Thought for today: `` Money often costs too much.'' _ <PERSON> Ralph </PERSON> <PERSON> Waldo </PERSON> <PERSON> Emerson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> essayist and poet -LRB- 1803-1882 -RRB-.
</TEXT>
