 `` The Midnight Hour'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Vidmark </ORGANIZATION>, VHS-Beta, $ 89.95 -RRB- `` The Midnight Hour'' is a good little vampire, witches and ghouls tale starring <PERSON> Shari </PERSON> <PERSON> Belafonte-Harper </PERSON> as a witch who brings terror to a small town on <LOCATION> Halloween </LOCATION>. Although there are recognizable names in the movie, the acting leaves much to be desired. Co-starring are: <PERSON> Levar </PERSON> <PERSON> Burton </PERSON>, <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Montgomery </PERSON>, <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Van </PERSON> <PERSON> Patten </PERSON>, <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> McCarthy </PERSON>, <PERSON> Jonelle </PERSON> <PERSON> Allen </PERSON>, <PERSON> Dedee </PERSON> <PERSON> Pfeifer </PERSON> and <PERSON> Cindy </PERSON> <PERSON> Morgan </PERSON>. And for a horror flick, the chills are as lacking as the thespian skills. Nonetheless, it is still an enjoyable romp as the the town's cemetery residents climb out of their graves and munch, rip and mutilate their way through the night, joining trick-or-treaters and crashing a halloween party The game then becomes how to get the baddies back in the grave and the townsfolk back to normal. Along the way, there are a few chuckles. And despite all its flaws, `` The Midnight Hour'' is an adequate little horror flick for a rainy Saturday afternoon. _ By <PERSON> Chris </PERSON> <PERSON> French </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer
