<HEAD>In the Groove: Record Reviews</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By STEVEN WINE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 `` The Telluride Sessions'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> MCA </ORGANIZATION> -RRB- _ Strength in Numbers Innovation and bluegrass are uneasy companions. But the all-star band Strength in Numbers is proof that the banjo, dobro, bass, fiddle and mandolin can break new ground. `` The Telluride Sessions'' combines bluegrass instrumentation with New Age melodies and classical-music arrangements, and the result is a pleasure to hear. These guys are n't just any pickers. <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> on mandolin and <PERSON> Bela </PERSON> <PERSON> Fleck </PERSON> on banjo are members of the New Grass Revival, one of the best progressive bluegrass bands. <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> -LRB- on fiddle, guitar and mandolin -RRB-, <PERSON> Jerry </PERSON> <PERSON> Douglas </PERSON> -LRB- dobro -RRB- and <PERSON> Edgar </PERSON> <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> -LRB- bass -RRB- are also terrific instrumentalists. But for their first record together, these inventive virtuosos decided to emphasize ensemble playing rather than solos. Themes are developed by unusual instrumental combinations _ two violins and a bowed bass, for example, on the beautiful `` One Winter's Night.'' Counterpoint and dynamics, rarely important in bluegrass music, are explored to great effect. The band has a lot of fun with syncopation, too. `` The Telluride Sessions'' is n't without dazzling solos. O'Connor -LRB- on guitar -RRB- and <PERSON> Fleck </PERSON> play with breathless speed on `` Slopes.'' <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> and <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> stage a mandolin duel on `` <LOCATION> Macedonia </LOCATION>.'' But the star of record may be its most unheralded participant. <PERSON> Meyer </PERSON> performs tricks on the bass that will leave listeners shaking their head, and he had a hand in most of the strongest compositions, including the good-humored `` Pink Flamingos'' and the pensive `` No Apologies.'' _ By <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Wine </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
