<FIRST>r f PM-BusinessHighlights     06-26 0787</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Business Highlights,0826</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> boosted to $ 12.2 billion its hostile takeover offer for media giant <ORGANIZATION> Time </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, which is pursuing its own bid for <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION> said Friday it was raising its initial $ 175-a-share offer for Time to $ 200 a share in cash Time, which rejected <ORGANIZATION> Paramount </ORGANIZATION>'s earlier $ 10.7 billion takeover bid as inadequate, said its board will consider the new offer `` in due course.''
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
