<HEAD>Sears Will Keep 6,000-Employee Subsidiary in Illinois</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New throughout to UPDATE with details and quotes; no pickup</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BRENDA C. COLEMAN</BYLINE>
<UNK>Associated Press Writer</UNK>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> Roebuck </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said today it will keep its 6,000-employee Merchandise Group in <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> but move it to a <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> suburb. `` We believe this Chicagoland location will serve the best interests of our company and its shareholders for decades to come,'' Chairman <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said in a statement released before a morning news conference. `` We anticipate that the move to the new facility will begin in 2 -LCB- to 3 years,'' he said. The site is in <LOCATION> Hoffman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Estates </LOCATION>, 20 miles northwest of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>. Last fall, the nation's largest retailer announced a restructuring plan that included selling the 110-story Sears Tower _ the world's tallest building _ and shifting the <ORGANIZATION> Merchandise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> and its 6,000 employees to less costly quarters. The announcement set off a bidding war between <LOCATION> Illinois </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Sunbelt </ORGANIZATION> states, especially <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Carolina </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>. The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> said <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> offered an incentive package worth an estimated $ 61 million to lure the <ORGANIZATION> Merchandise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> to a 200-acre site in <LOCATION> Hoffman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Estates </LOCATION>. The newspaper said local tax breaks to <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> will be worth an estimated $ 178 million. `` The total proposal that was worked out is extremely competitive with alternative sites,'' <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said. The Hoffman Estates site is part of an undeveloped 1,300 acres north of the <LOCATION> Northwest </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Tollway </LOCATION> at <ORGANIZATION> Illinois </ORGANIZATION> 59. <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> said it had signed a contract to purchase 700 acres along the tollway, including an outdoor music theater, <LOCATION> Poplar </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Creek </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> said the theater will continue operating. The <ORGANIZATION> Hoffman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Estates </ORGANIZATION> parcel was selected from about 50 sites in the <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> area and other states, <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said. <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> estimates that building a campus-style facility in <ORGANIZATION> Hoffman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Estates </ORGANIZATION> will cost about $ 220 million. The development will eventually generate an estimated $ 11 million a year in property taxes. <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON> said future commercial development of the site also is planned. The Tribune and the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Sun-Times </ORGANIZATION> said the deal was cemented Sunday after talks between Illinois Gov. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON> and <PERSON> Brennan </PERSON>. When the <ORGANIZATION> Merchandise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> move is completed, about 600 employees of <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> corporate staff will remain in the downtown <ORGANIZATION> Sears </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tower </ORGANIZATION>, the company said.
