<HEAD>Hasbro Chief Executive Dies; Takeover Speculation Arises</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Toy executive <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hassenfeld </PERSON>, chairman and chief executive of <ORGANIZATION> Hasbro </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, was praised Monday as unequaled among his peers, but his death left questions about the company's future. <PERSON> Hassenfeld </PERSON>, 47, died of pneumonia and cardiac arrest Sunday night at <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Presbyterian </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hospital </LOCATION>, where he had been hospitalized for four weeks, said <ORGANIZATION> Hasbro </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Wayne </PERSON> <PERSON> Charness </PERSON>. `` I believe that within the next year, you will see the company sold. It's an attractive property in the industry,'' said <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> Valentine </PERSON>, an analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Poor </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Valentine </PERSON> said he expected <PERSON> Hassenfeld </PERSON>'s family, which owns 13.1 percent of the Pawtucket-based toymaker, eventually would re-examine its position `` With <PERSON> Stephen </PERSON> gone and the company now a larger, more bureaucratic organization, the fun has probably gone out of this business for the <PERSON> Hassenfeld </PERSON> family,'' he said. Valentine estimated the sale price at $ 32 per share, but higher if the company performs better than expected this year. <ORGANIZATION> Hasbro </ORGANIZATION> common stock closed at $ 22.25, up 25, cents on the American Exchange Monday. Its volume of nearly 1.2 million shares made it the second most heavily traded issue on the exchange. But, said analyst <PERSON> Walter </PERSON> <PERSON> Kirchberger </PERSON> at <ORGANIZATION> PaineWebber </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </OR