ts have agreed to display the emblem, he said. In exchange, the restaurants are mentioned in advertisements appearing in the <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> area over four months. `` We are not paying them anything at all,'' <PERSON> Zuke </PERSON> said. Half of the sign contains a smoking cigarette against a background of green. The non-smoker half of the sign is red. <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Morris </PERSON> said it chose <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> to launch the campaign because of the number of letters it said it received from customers confused by a smoking ordinance that took effect last year. More customers wrote from <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> than from any other city that restricts smoking in public places, <PERSON> Zuke </PERSON> said.
